Ke7 16. O-O Nc4 17. Rfe1 d6 $15 {Lan,Z (2345)-Moiseenko,A (2678) China 2017 (1/
2-1/2, 74)}) 9... Nxd2 10. Qxd2 ({The point behind 5...Nc6 is that} 10. Nxd2
Nxd4 {wins a pawn.}) 10... Qxc4 {There have been many tries to prove
compensation for White based on his advance in development. But since Black
does not have weaknesses, he can count on retaining his extra pawn.} 11. O-O (
11. a3 {Preventing ...Qb4.} d5 (11... O-O 12. O-O Qb5 13. Rfc1 Qb6 14. b4 a5
15. Rab1 axb4 16. axb4 d5 17. Qc3 Bd7 18. b5 Na7 19. Ne5 Be8 20. Qxc7 Qxc7 21.
Rxc7 Nxb5 22. Rxb7 Nxd4 $15 {Rojicek,V (2406)-Hracek,Z (2624) Czechia 2012 (1/
2-1/2, 60)}) 12. O-O a5 13. Rac1 Qb3 14. e4 O-O 15. e5 a4 16. Rc5 Qb6 17. Qc2
h6 $15 18. g4 f5 $1 19. exf6 Rxf6 20. Rd1 Bd7 $17 {Javakhishvili,L (2454)
-Sutovsky,E (2703) Caleta 2012 (0-1, 39)}) 11... Qb4 12. Qd3 d5 13. Rfc1 Bd7 (
13... Qe7 14. Rc5 O-O 15. Rac1 Bd7 16. h4 Nb4 17. Qb3 Na6 18. R5c3 Rfb8 19. e3
c6 20. Bf1 Nc7 21. Bd3 Ne8 22. a4 a5 23. e4 dxe4 24. Bxe4 Nf6 25. Bb1 Nd5 $15 {
Piket,J (2615)-Adams,M (2590) Roquebrune 1992 (0-1, 60)}) 14. Rc2 Qe7 15. a3
O-O 16. Rac1 a5 17. h4 h6 18. e4 Rfd8 $5 19. e5 Rf8 $5 20. Qe3 a4 21. Nh2 f5
22. exf6 Qxf6 {White's compensation (if there is even any) does not allow him
